  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely grate the <strong>ginger</strong>, then combine it in a bowl with the<strong> soy sauce</strong> – this is your <strong>ginger soy marinade</strong></p><p>Place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>and slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> thinner pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-chicken-ramen/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced chicken</strong> to the <strong>ginger soy marinade</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Line a baking tray with <strong>baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chicken</strong> to the tray and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-chicken-ramen/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, peel and slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>(as finely as you can!)</p><p>Slice the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Tip: Deseed them if you can't handle the heat!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-chicken-ramen/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>finely</p><p>Cut 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime </strong>into wedges</p><p>Pick the <strong>coriander leaves</strong> from the stalks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-chicken-ramen/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>Kallo chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and <strong>Sriracha hot chilli sauce</strong> in 500ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> spicy ramen base</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>spicy ramen base</strong> to a pot over a very-low heat and cook for 5-6 min or until warmed through</p><p>Re-boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-chicken-ramen/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>medium egg noodles</strong> to a separate pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-chicken-ramen/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>cooked chicken</strong> from the oven and slice it finely</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-chicken-ramen/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained noodles</strong> to deep bowls and pour over the <strong>spicy ramen base</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> sliced chicken, sliced red chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a handful of <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>red onion</strong>, <strong>spring onion</strong>, <strong>coriander leaves</strong> and a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
